[0.015, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand make it read cleanly: I should be able to open the file and know exactly what it does.\u001b[39m                            \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                        \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                        \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mWhen you're done, write SUMMARY.md in the current directory: a few sentences on what you built, whether it compiled \u001b[39m  \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand ran on the first try, the program output, and anything about Promise that surprised you or that you had to work \u001b[39m  \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mout (it is not in your training data). Promise is young — if something about the language or its standard library \u001b[39m    \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mmade the task harder than it should be, or you wished a thing worked differently, say so; that feedback is as much \u001b[39m   \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2"]
[0.000, "o", ";255;255;255mthe point as the working program.\u001b[39m                                                                                     \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                        \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mTwo kinds of rough edge are worth capturing in their own file for filing upstream — don't quietly work around either:\u001b[39m \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                        \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf you hit a compiler bug, minimize it first: bisect to the smallest source that still triggers it, and find the \u001b[39m     \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mclosest variant that *does* compile, so the trigger is pinned down precisely (not just \"my big program failed\"). Then\u001b[39m \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mwrite it to a `BUG-<slug>.md` file in the project root with a one-line title, the `promise version` output, your \u001b[39m     \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mplatform, the "]
[0.000, "o", "minimal repro (smallest `.pr` source plus the exact `promise build` command), the verbatim error \u001b[39m       \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255moutput, the expected behavior, a short table of what does and doesn't trigger it, your best guess at the cause, and \u001b[39m  \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mthe workaround you used in the real code. Verify the repro actually fails and the \"compiles fine\" controls actually \u001b[39m  \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mcompile before writing them down — don't go from memory.\u001b[39m                                                              \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                        \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf the task needs something Promise doesn't have yet — a standard-library module that isn't there, or a missing \u001b[39m      \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mlanguage feature — don't fake it silently. Build the closest clean thing you can, or, if it's a hard blocker, stop \u001b[39m   \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand say why. "]
[0.000, "o", "Either way record the gap in a `FEATURE-<slug>.md` file in the project root: a one-line title, the \u001b[39m      \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255m`promise version` output, what you needed and why the task called for it, what's missing (e.g. no standard module for\u001b[39m \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mX, no language support for Y), whether it blocked you outright or just forced a workaround, the workaround you used,\u001b[39m  \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand — if you can — a **sketch of the API or syntax** that would have made it clean.\u001b[39m                                   \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                        \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mPut `Please file this upstream at https://github.com/promise-language/promise/issues` at the top of any such file, \u001b[39m   \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mwrite one file per distinct issue, and mention each in your summary so I remember to submit it. Only write these for \u001b[39m \r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mreal failures "]
[0.000, "o", "and real gaps — don't invent them.\u001b[39m                                                                      \r\u001b[2B\u001b[49m\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m✳\u001b[3GForming… \r\u001b[3B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m❯ \u001b[39m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[44C\u001b[2B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mesc to interrupt\u001b[39m\u001b[36;1H\u001b[34;3H"]
