[0.000, "o", "row-call-then-move\", not failable-specific. L\u001b[61Gt\u001b[63Gme pin whether it's tied to \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m~string\u001b[99G\u001b[39mparams or any owned\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bvalue.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[4BF8 is \u001b[10Gtriking — even\u001b[25G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249m.clone()\u001b[39m after \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mlook(path)\u001b[39m is rejected. This\u001b[69Ghinges \u001b[77Gn whether plain \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mstring p\u001b[39m is\u001b[105Gtruly a borrow\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B(as \u001b[8Ghe\u001b[11Gguide says) or actually consumes. Th\u001b[48G decisive tes\u001b[62G: does an \u001b[73Gxplic\u001b[80G \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m&\u001b[83G\u001b[39mborrow param behave differe\u001b[111Gtly?\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m \u001b[3G\u001b[39mRunning\u001b[11G\u001b[1m1\u001b[13G\u001b[22mshell\u001b[19Gcommand…\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m  ⎿  $ cd /tmp/bugv\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mv () { echo \"### $1\"; cat > main.pr; promise build 2>&1 | head -5; echo \"(exit ${PIPESTATUS[0]})\"; echo; }\r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[3G  \u001b[6G\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mv \"G1: plain 'string p' param, call then move — fails?\" <<'EOF'\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B   \u001b[38;2;153;153;153mtype R { string s; }\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38"]
