[0.000, "o", "l (`main.pr`) that takes file paths as arguments and counts the\r\u001b[7C\u001b[1B\u001b[2m6\u001b[10G\u001b[22mlines in each, **one goroutine per file**, then prints a per-file count and a grand\r\u001b[7C\u001b[1B\u001b[2m7\u001b[10G\u001b[22mtotal. Each goroutine sends its result down a `channel[FileCount]`; `main` gathers them\r\u001b[7C\u001b[1B\u001b[2m8\u001b[10G\u001b[22minto a `map[int, FileCount]` keyed by the file's argument index so the output is printed\r\u001b[7C\u001b[1B\u001b[2m9\u001b[10G\u001b[22min the original argument order even though\u001b[53Ggoroutines\u001b[64Gfini\u001b[69Gh in any order. Unreadable\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[6C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;248;248;242m\u001b[2m10\u001b[10G\u001b[22mf\u001b[12Gl\u001b[16G(missing, n\u001b[28G permissio\u001b[39G,\u001b[41Getc.) are caught\u001b[58Gwith a\u001b[65G`? \u001b[69G { ...\u001b[76G}` handler and reported\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m… +70 lines \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m⏺\u001b[3G\u001b[39mLet me do a final read of \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mmain.pr\u001b[39m to confirm it reads cleanly as a finished artifact.\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m⏺\u001b[3G\u001b[39mReading \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m file…\u001b[36;1H\u001b[34;3H"]
